The evidence with the title 'Who inspects what? A food safety scramble | Food Safety News ' says Dec 16, 2010  ... Two government agencies , the U.S. Department Of Agriculture and the Food And Drug Administration, share most of the responsibility of food safety inspection.  ... Technically , the USDA is responsible for the safety of meat, poultry and egg products, while the FDA regulates all other foods, Raymond explains. 
